      "Develop Working Memory Through Brain Training: Use tools like dual n-back, Lumosity, or memory-challenging games to strengthen working memory capacity, which supports faster and sharper context re-engagement.",
      "Reduce Emotional Attachment to Task Completion: Practice mindfulness or emotional regulation techniques to become less emotionally anchored to completing one task before starting another, increasing tolerance for ambiguity.",
      "Create Visual Cue Systems: Use color-coding, sticky notes, or digital dashboards that signal task urgency and type, this helps orient the brain rapidly when returning to interrupted tasks.",
      "Reflect on Task Switches Daily: At the end of each day, log how many task shifts occurred and evaluate what helped or hindered performance. This promotes metacognitive awareness and faster learning.",
      "Strengthen Attention Recovery Speed: Practice micro-meditations (1\u20132 minutes of focused breathing) after each task switch to accelerate mental clarity and reboot focus faster.",
