      "Starts each day with a structured plan, laying out tasks and timelines clearly in advance.",
      "Uses tools like planners, digital boards, or checklists consistently to track progress and deadlines.",
      "Breaks large assignments into logical, sequenced steps to avoid confusion or rework.",
      "Keeps work areas, both physical and digital, neat, labeled, and arranged for quick access and clarity.",
      "Prioritizes tasks based on urgency and importance, ensuring critical work is handled at peak productivity times.",
      "Ends each day by reviewing accomplishments and setting priorities for the next day.",
      "Focuses on one task at a time, reducing switching between unrelated activities to maintain flow and efficiency.",
      "Follows consistent naming conventions and documentation habits to maintain traceability and standardization.",
