      "Feels psychologically comfortable in ambiguous or evolving situations, with minimal anxiety or defensiveness when conditions change.",
      "Regulates emotional responses such as frustration or fear during disruptions, enabling calm and rational choices.",
      "Views change not as a threat to competence or identity but as a chance to grow, explore new approaches, and step outside the comfort zone.",
      "Responds constructively and promptly when unexpected events or alterations occur, maintaining functional engagement and momentum.",
      "Adjusts behavior seamlessly across different teams, roles, or cultural settings without losing effectiveness or clarity.",
      "Actively seeks benefits or learning opportunities in disruptions and, where appropriate, champions change by encouraging others to adapt and innovate.",
      "Integrates feedback quickly, even when it contradicts previous directions, and realigns actions without rigid attachment.",
      "Performs well without relying on structure or predictability, remaining composed when routines are disrupted.",
      "Adapts personal style to work effectively with different individuals, tailoring communication and interaction to meet diverse preferences and needs."
